…tion (#538)

Adds tests/unit/issue_538.rs covering the concrete verifiable core of
issue #538:

- every tomato surface (tomato/tomatoes, помидор/помидоры, томат/томаты)
  pins its grammatical number as singular or plural, from the seed data;
- each surface exposes its part of speech (noun);
- each surface denotes the tomato meaning (bidirectional word<->meaning);
- singular and plural are two distinct surfaces in each language, closing
  the reported помидор-has-a-plural-but-томат-does-not asymmetry;
- grammatical_number / singular / plural are grounded (Q104083 / Q110786 /
  Q146786) and lexicalised in en/ru/hi/zh.
